1. login: logs in as a user
whoami: prints username
passwd: changes user's password
su: runs new session as user inside current session
logout: logs current user logout

2. login -f student

3. sudo -u pietjepuk whoami

4. passwd d1t15een5uperve1l1gw@chtw00rd

5. done!

6. exit

2.2
1. vi gisteren

2. cat gisteren gisteren

3. cat gisteren gisteren gisteren > gisteren3

4. pgup, pgdown, G, home, /, n, q

5. ping -i .2 localhost | less

6. /dev/random < less

7. cut: select file columns
sort: sort lines of text file 
head: shows first lines of text file 
tail: shows last lines of text file 
wc: counts words / lines / characters 

8. sort -r gisteren

9. cut -c -1 

10. wc -l gisteren3

11 head -n 5

12 tail -n 3

13 head -n 5 gisteren3 | tail -n 3 | wc -m

